# 5 Design Tools Every Vibe Coder / Creative Developer Should Know

## 1. Spline (3D Engine for Web)

https://spline.design/

- Free plan available
- Paid: ~$12–$20/month
- What it does: Real-time interactive 3D inside browser
- Key features:
    - 3D scenes, lighting, animations
    - Export + embed directly into websites
    - No-code interactions

👉 Use for: Hero sections, product demos, scroll-based storytelling

## 2. Unicorn Studio (Motion Layer for Web)

https://www.unicorn.studio/

- Free + paid plans (for export/customization)
- What it does: WebGL animations without coding
- Key features:
    - Pre-built animation effects
    - Remix templates
    - Embed into Webflow / custom sites

👉 Use for: Premium feel (this is what separates average vs luxury websites

## 3. Manus (AI Website Builder)

https://manus.im/

- Early-stage (pricing evolving / limited access)
- What it does: Prompt → full website
- Key features:
    - Generates layout + copy + structure
    - Rapid MVP creation
    - Idea → live site in minutes

👉 Use for: Fast prototyping & landing pages

## 4. 21st.dev (Frontend Acceleration)

https://21st.dev/home

- Mostly free + premium UI kits
- What it does: Ready-to-use React components
- Key features:
    - Copy-paste UI blocks
    - Clean, production-ready code
    - Saves dev time massively

👉 Use for: Building faster without reinventing UI

## 5. Landing.love (Conversion Library)

https://www.landing.love/

- Free + paid inspiration packs
- What it does: 2,000+ real landing pages
- Key features:
    - Proven UI patterns
    - Animation references
    - High-converting layouts

👉 Use for: Research before building anything

# How To Use The Tools :

## 1. Spline.design

**Use for:** 3D hero sections, product mockups, interactive website visuals.

**Pricing:** Free plan available. Paid plans start at **$12/seat/month billed annually**.

**How to use:**

1. Open Spline.
2. Choose a starter 3D scene or blank canvas.
3. Add 3D objects, lighting, materials, camera movement.
4. Add interactions like hover, click, drag, or scroll.
5. Export/embed it into your website.

**Best prompt/template:**

> Create a premium 3D hero visual for a SaaS website about [product]. Use a clean futuristic style, soft lighting, floating UI cards, smooth depth, minimal colors, and make it suitable for embedding above the fold.
> 

## 2. Unicorn.studio

**Use for:** WebGL animations, background effects, interactive website motion.

**Pricing:** Free plan available. Paid “Legend” plan is **$20/month or $168/year**.

**How to use:**

1. Pick an effect/template.
2. Customize colors, particles, glow, blur, motion.
3. Adjust animation speed and layout.
4. Export or embed into Framer/Webflow/custom code.

**Best prompt/template:**

> Create a luxury animated website background for [brand/type]. Use subtle particles, soft gradients, elegant motion, low distraction, and make it feel premium without hurting readability.
> 

## 3. Manus.im

**Use for:** AI-generated websites, MVPs, landing pages, business websites.

**Pricing:** Uses a credit-based system; official docs mention flexible plans and usage-based credits.

**How to use:**

1. Describe your website idea clearly.
2. Mention audience, sections, style, CTA, and goal.
3. Let Manus generate the first version.
4. Edit copy, layout, colors, and sections.
5. Publish or export depending on available options.

**Best prompt/template:**

> Build a high-converting landing page for [business/product]. Target audience: [audience]. Goal: [leads/sales/signups]. Style: [premium/minimal/bold]. Include hero, problem, benefits, proof, pricing, FAQ, and CTA. Make the copy sharp, conversion-focused, and mobile-first.
> 

## 4. 21st.dev

**Use for:** Copy-paste React/Next.js components.

**Pricing:** The public community library offers thousands of React components; pricing depends on specific creators/packs.

**How to use:**

1. Search for the component you need.
2. Pick navbar, pricing, hero, cards, testimonials, etc.
3. Copy the code.
4. Paste into your React/Next.js project.
5. Customize Tailwind classes, copy, spacing, and colors.

**Best prompt/template for Cursor:**

> Update this component to match my brand: colors [colors], font style [style], tone [premium/minimal/bold]. Keep the layout responsive, improve spacing, add hover states, and make it production-ready without changing the core structure.
> 

## 5. Landing.love

**Use for:** Landing page inspiration, animation references, layout ideas.

**Pricing:** 100% free, according to its About page.

**How to use:**

1. Browse by category: SaaS, AI, portfolio, agency, ecommerce.
2. Save 3–5 references.
3. Study hero structure, CTA placement, animations, and section order.
4. Use it to create your design direction before building.

**Best prompt/template:**

> Analyze this landing page reference and extract the design system: hero layout, CTA style, section flow, typography, animation ideas, color mood, and conversion patterns. Then turn it into a wireframe for my [business type] website.
>
